   const handler = createTitleUpdateHandler({ bus, buffer, initCtx });
   await bus.call('http:register-route', initCtx, {
     method: 'GET',
     path: '/api/chat/titles/:conversationId',
     handler,
   });
   ```

2. **Handler Signature** (same as chat-stream):
   ```typescript
   async (req: HttpRequest, res: HttpResponse): Promise<void> => {
     // Auth, open stream, subscribe to title-update event, write frames
   }
   ```

3. **Streaming Response**:
   ```typescript
   const stream = res.status(200).stream({
     contentType: 'text/event-stream; charset=utf-8',
   });
   stream.onClose(() => { /* cleanup */ });
   bus.subscribe('conversations:title-updated', key, (ctx, { title }) => {
     if (ctx.conversationId === conversationId) {
       stream.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify({ title })}\n\n`);
     }
   });
   ```

4. **Client Consumer** (same fetch pattern as chat-stream):
   ```typescript
   const resp = await fetch(`/api/chat/titles/${conversationId}`, {
     headers: { accept: 'text/event-stream' },
     credentials: 'include',
   });
   // Parse SSE frames, update UI on `{ title: "..." }` frames
   ```

5. **Wiring**: Route registers during channel-web plugin init (already in preset load order). No new preset entry needed if reusing channel-web plugin; otherwise push new plugin after http-server but before agents (order doesn't matter once http-server is ready).

---

## Key Files Reference

| Component | File Path | Purpose |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| HTTP Server | `/packages/http-server/src/plugin.ts` | Registers routes, manages listeners, streaming impl |
| Types | `/packages/http-server/src/types.ts` | HttpRequest, HttpResponse, StreamingResponse interfaces |
| SSE Handler Factory | `/packages/channel-web/src/server/sse.ts` | GET /api/chat/stream/:reqId — the gold standard |
| Transport | `/packages/channel-web/src/lib/transport.ts` | Browser fetch SSE consumer |
| Chat Routes | `/packages/channel-web/src/server/routes-chat.ts` | Examples of route registration |
| Channel-Web Plugin | `/packages/channel-web/src/server/plugin.ts` | Route registration pattern |
| K8s Preset | `/presets/k8s/src/index.ts` | Plugin wiring and load order |
| Titles Plugin | `/packages/conversation-titles/src/plugin.ts` | Title generation (integration point) |

This precedent is production-proven: the chat-stream endpoint handles multi-tab subscribers, proxies, client disconnects, and message replay through the same mechanism that title updates would use.

